H.B. 820
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Apr 8, 2025
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH40265-MRa-101
Short Title: Prescription Eye Drop Early Refill Coverage. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Reeder.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO REQUIRE HEALTH BENEFIT PLANS THAT PROVIDE COVERAGE FOR
3 PRESCRIPTION EYE DROPS TO ALSO PROVIDE COVERAGE FOR EARLY
4 REFILLS.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1.(a) Article 3 of Chapter 58 of the General Statutes is amended by adding
7 a new section to read:
8 "§ 58-3-266. Coverage for early refills of prescription eye drops.
9 Every health benefit plan offered by an insurer in this State that provides coverage for
10 prescription eye drops shall not deny coverage for a refill of an eye drop prescription if both of
11 the following conditions apply:
12 (1) For a 30-day supply, the patient requested the refill after either of the
13 following:
14 a. The passage of an amount of time after which a patient should have
15 used seventy percent (70%) of the dosage units of the drug according
16 to a health care provider's instructions.
17 b. Twenty-one days after either (i) the original date the prescription was
18 distributed to the insured or (ii) the date the most recent refill was
19 distributed to the insured.
20 (2) The refill requested by the insured would not exceed the limit, if any, on the
21 number of refills for that prescription that the prescribing health care provider
22 indicated on the original prescription."
23 SECTION 1.(b) G.S. 135-48.51 reads as rewritten:
24 "§ 135-48.51. Coverage and operational mandates related to Chapter 58 of the General
25 Statutes.
26 The following provisions of Chapter 58 of the General Statutes apply to the State Health Plan:
27 …
28 (9a) G.S. 58-3-266, Coverage for early refills of prescription eye drops.
29 …."
30 SECTION 1.(c) Subsection (a) of this section becomes effective October 1, 2025,
31 and applies to contracts issued, renewed, or amended on or after that date. Subsection (b) of this
32 section applies as of the start of the next plan year following that date.
33 SECTION 2. Effective July 1, 2025, there is appropriated from the General Fund to
34 the Department of State Treasurer the sum of one hundred thousand dollars ($100,000) in
35 recurring funds for each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium to be used to provide the coverage
36 required under Section 1(b) of this act.
*DRH40265-MRa-101*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 SECTION 3. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
2 law.
